{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We annotated four types of entities corresponding to UMLS ® [5] semantic groups (SG) of pathologies (DISO), anatomic entities (ANAT), biochemical or pharmacological substances (CHEM) and lab tests, diagnostic or therapeutic procedures (PROC).For a first version of the corpus, and given the budget and time constraints, we focused on the most relevant subset of UMLS groups for the task.",
    "Table 3 shows the list of annotated SGs, the correspondence to UMLS ® semantic types, and examples.",
    "Note that we annotated all these types of entities, regardless of whether they occurred in negated contexts or not.",
    "For example, ostomía ('ostomy') is annotated in sin ostomía ('without ostomy').",
    "Qualifiers or modifiers were only annotated as part of a broader entity (and with the same label) provided that the full entity could be normalized to a reference terminology or code."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We annotated four types of entities corresponding to UMLS ® [5] semantic groups (SG) of pathologies (DISO), anatomic entities (ANAT), biochemical or pharmacological substances (CHEM) and lab tests, diagnostic or therapeutic procedures (PROC).For a first version of the corpus, and given the budget and time constraints, we focused on the most relevant subset of UMLS groups for the task."
  ]
